port of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, sand, grits etc. They are used in filling tall bauxite and alumina silos.\n\n<b>Slurry Pumps</b>\n\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to these requirements.\n\n<b>Rod Mills</b>\n\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\n\n<b>Ball Mills</b>\n\nThese are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for calcining or Alumina refining Process. These are also used in Coke Grinding for Carbon Paste preparation in Aluminium Smelters.\n\n<b>Thickeners</b>\n\nThese are used to concentrate alumina Slurry (30-35% Solids) from refinery to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into circuit whereas the underflow is taken for evaporation circuit or to tailings as reject disposal.\n\n<b>Flotation </b>\n\nWe can offer the Beneficiation/Up gradation solution for the Bauxite ore through flotation as part of total solution for this plant which will include Crushing, Grinding, Flotation, thickening, dewatering     (Filtration), slurry pumping and system integration and plant design.', 'BAUXITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '623-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:24:04', '2015-02-02 00:24:04', '', 623, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/623-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(624, 2, '2015-01-31 06:16:51', '2015-01-31 06:16:51', '<b>Jaw Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used as primary crushers in Bauxite Plants and also for spent anode butts.\r\n\r\n<b>Apron Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<b>Apron Conveyors</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for conveying spent Anode Butts for recycling in Anode Paste Plants and are quite similar to Apron feeders in many respects, however these may be of curved alignment and long lengths (say up to 100 M).\r\n\r\n<b>Double Roll Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in crushing spent anodes in Anode Paste Plants of Aluminium Smelters.\r\n\r\n<b>Conveyor Components</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<b>Motorised Trippers</b>\r\n\r\nBasically these are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<b>Grizzly Screens/ Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Bauxite Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<b>Rotary Disc Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material e.g. coke breeze, ground bauxite, alumina etc. from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment.\r\n\r\n<b>Circular Motion Screens</b>\r\n\r\nAlso known as CM Screens, these are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants as also in beneficiation plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<b>Linear Motion Screens</b>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>High Particle Acceleration Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for heavy and very heavy screening applications for fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Banana Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two/ three deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<b>Cone Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell these equipment, which are required as Secondary (-150/ 75 mm) and Tertiary Crushers (-30/ 10 mm) in Bauxite Crushing for Alumina production.\r\n\r\n<b>Reciprocating Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores\r\n\r\n<b>Bucket Elevators</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for vertical transport of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, sand, grits etc. They are used in filling tall bauxite and alumina silos.\r\n\r\n<b>Slurry Pumps</b>\r\n\r\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to these requirements.\r\n\r\n<b>Rod Mills</b>\r\n\r\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<b>Ball Mills</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for calcining or Alumina refining Process. These are also used in Coke Grinding for Carbon Paste preparation in Aluminium Smelters.\r\n\r\n<b>Thickeners</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used to concentrate alumina Slurry (30-35% Solids) from refinery to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into circuit whereas the underflow is taken for evaporation circuit or to tailings as reject disposal.\r\n\r\n<b>Flotation </b>\r\n\r\nWe can offer the Beneficiation/Up gradation solution for the Bauxite ore through flotation as part of total solution for this plant which will include Crushing, Grinding, Flotation, thickening, dewatering     (Filtration), slurry pumping and system integration and plant design.', 'BAUXITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '623-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-31 06:16:51', '2015-01-31 06:16:51', '', 623, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/623-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(625, 2, '2015-01-31 06:17:48', '2015-01-31 06:17:48', '<b>Mineral Beneficiation is defined as the process of separating valuable minerals from waste gangue material in the mined ores. MSEL serves mineral beneficiation sectors of mining and minerals industry by supplying various equipment needed in beneficiation circuit as listed below.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>CM Screens</b>\r\n\r\nAlso known as Circular Motion Screens, these are used to segregate various size fractions in coal/lignite streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to power plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<b>LM Screens</b>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used in similar situations as above but where the height is limited by surrounding facilities, for the screening of small and short fractions and required throughput is high.\r\n\r\n<b>Roller Screens</b>\r\n\r\nAs opposed to above two types which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in screening Run of Mine ore when feed stream consists of difficult sticky clayey moist materials and would choke and blind the screen apertures of normal screening machines.\r\n\r\n<b>Grizzly Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese Feeders are used to reclaim feed stream from storage bins/ hoppers where the materials are not easy to handle (wet, clayey or lot of ash content), having size fractions ranging from big lumps to significantly high percentage of wet/moist fines and where scalping is also needed.\r\n\r\n<b>Motorised Trippers</b>\r\n\r\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\r\n\r\n<b>Roll Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nSingle Roll Crushers are used to crush ROM Ore (1500 mm- 1000 mm size) to (-) 300-200 mm size. In Ore Preparation Plants the feed is to be further crushed to (-) 25 mm size by using Toothed Double Roll Crushers. Smooth DR Crushers can be used for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\r\n\r\n<b>Cone Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell these equipment, which are required in tertiary crushing (-30/10 mm) of various ores for subsequent grinding to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Impactors</b>\r\n\r\nFor higher capacities and crushing to (-) 5mm, impactors/hammer mills are used.\r\n\r\n<b>Reciprocating Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used to reclaim ore from surge bins/bunkers to feed crushers or conveyors typically up to 1000 tph.\r\n\r\n<b>Rotary Disc Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. These can be used in chemical conditioning slurry tanks for dosing reagents.\r\n\r\n<b>Slurry Pumps</b>\r\n\r\nIn mines and ore handling plants these are used for dewatering the sump pits. In beneficiation plants these are used in conveying ore slurries from and to various units of beneficiation circuit.\r\n\r\n<b>Thickeners</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in Beneficiation Circuits to dewater/ thicken coal/reject slurries for further processing use.\r\n\r\n<b>Column Flotation Cells</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in beneficiation of Ore fines (&lt; 100 microns) where gravity and conventional flotation are not effective.\r\n\r\n<b>U Flotation Cells</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used to concentrate and separate valuable minerals from gangue minerals or from other valuable minerals in beneficiation circuits.\r\n\r\n<b>Apron Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size Coal from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\n\r\n<b>Conveyor Components</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<b>Drum Scrubbers</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used to clean clayey/siliceous coatings from iron ore lumps as the first stage of Iron Ore Beneficiation.\r\n\r\n<b>High Particle Acceleration Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for heavy and very heavy screening applications for fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Roller Screens</b>\r\n\r\nAs opposed to above three types of screens which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in Iron Ore Pellet Plants when it is essential to prevent breakage and degradation of pellets and efficient separation of fines for recycling back to pelletisers.\r\n\r\n<b>Grizzly Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Iron Ore Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.', 'MINERAL BENEFICIATION', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mineral-beneficiation', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:27:44', '2015-02-02 00:27:44', '', 0, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/?page_id=625', 0, 'page', '', 0),
