(685, 2, '2015-02-02 00:21:30', '2015-02-02 00:21:30', '<b>Apron Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<b>Jaw Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used as primary crushers in Rock Phosphate Mining. Normally Single Toggles are preferred.\r\n\r\n<b>Roll Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nToothed Double Roll Crushers are used as secondary crushers in Rock Phosphate plants to crush (-) 25 mm size. Smooth DR Crushers can be used for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\r\n\r\n<b>Cone Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell these equipment, which are required in tertiary crushing (-30/10 mm) of Rock Phosphate for subsequent grinding to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\n<b>Chain Mills</b>\r\n\r\nThese are special size reduction equipment in Fertiliser segment for reducing (-) 75 mm feed to (-) 6mm lumps.\r\n\r\n<b>Conveyor Components</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<b>Reciprocating Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores.\r\n\r\n<b>Motorised Trippers</b>\r\n\r\nBasically these are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<b>Grizzly Screens/ Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Rock Phosphate Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Circular Motion Screens</b>\r\n\r\nAlso known as CM Screens, these are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants as also in beneficiation plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<b>High Particle Acceleration Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for heavy and very heavy screening applications for fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH.  In Iron Ore &amp; Steel industry these are used for fine screening in Flux Crushing &amp; Screening circuits. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Slurry Pumps</b>\r\n\r\nIn Rock Phosphate beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to these requirements.\r\n\r\n<b>Rod Mills</b>\r\n\r\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<b>Ball Mills</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for downstream Ore beneficiation.\r\n\r\n<b>U Flotation Cells</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for Silica removal as underflow in first stage of flotation, whereas Phosphates and Carbonates are extracted as froth.\r\n\r\nIn second stage additional bank of these flotation cells are used to remove carbonate (rejects) as froth and Phosphate Concentrates as underflow, which is then processed through cleaner flotation Cells before taking for thickener concentration and filtration.\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Banana Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<b>Thickeners</b>\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>These are used to concentrate silica Slurry (30-35% Solids) underflow from first flotation stage  to about 60- 70 % Solids before sending Thickener underflow to tailings disposal as rejects. Thickener Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into grinding circuit.</li>\r\n	<li>Another set of thickeners are used to process Carbonate froth from Second stage flotation, recycling the thickener overflow as Process water and sending thickener underflow as tailings for reject disposal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Vibrating Tube Mills</b>\r\n\r\nVibrating Tube Mills are for continuous or batch grinding of materials to a very fine end product. Two vibrating/ grinding cylinders are placed either directly above the other or inclined at 30 degrees to perpendicular. Located between the two tubes, an eccentrically supported weight is driven to produce a small circular vibration. The tubes are charged with ball or rod media to aid in the grinding action (attrition) from the constant impulses. Material is ground as it travels from the input end of the tube to the outlet end.\r\n\r\nThese Mills have a very small size and low energy consumption compared to other mill types and are used in manufacture of paints and varnishes where ultra- fines (of the order 10-20 microns) are required. Output is restricted to 5-10 tph. We offer these from our Baroda plant.', 'ROCK PHOSPHATE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '621-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:21:30', '2015-02-02 00:21:30', '', 621, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/621-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(690, 2, '2015-02-02 00:24:25', '2015-02-02 00:24:25', '<b>Jaw Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used as primary crushers in Bauxite Plants and also for spent anode butts.\r\n\r\n<b>Apron Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<b>Apron Conveyors</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for conveying spent Anode Butts for recycling in Anode Paste Plants and are quite similar to Apron feeders in many respects, however these may be of curved alignment and long lengths (say up to 100 M).\r\n\r\n<b>Double Roll Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in crushing spent anodes in Anode Paste Plants of Aluminium Smelters.\r\n\r\n<b>Conveyor Components</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<b>Motorised Trippers</b>\r\n\r\nBasically these are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<b>Grizzly Screens/ Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Bauxite Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<b>Rotary Disc Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material e.g. coke breeze, ground bauxite, alumina etc. from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment.\r\n\r\n<b>Circular Motion Screens</b>\r\n\r\nAlso known as CM Screens, these are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants as also in beneficiation plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<b>Linear Motion Screens</b>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>High Particle Acceleration Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for heavy and very heavy screening applications for fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Banana Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two/ three deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<b>Cone Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell these equipment, which are required as Secondary (-150/ 75 mm) and Tertiary Crushers (-30/ 10 mm) in Bauxite Crushing for Alumina production.\r\n\r\n<b>Reciprocating Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores\r\n\r\n<b>Bucket Elevators</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for vertical transport of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, sand, grits etc. They are used in filling tall bauxite and alumina silos.\r\n\r\n<b>Slurry Pumps</b>\r\n\r\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to these requirements.\r\n\r\n<b>Rod Mills</b>\r\n\r\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<b>Ball Mills</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for calcining or Alumina refining Process. These are also used in Coke Grinding for Carbon Paste preparation in Aluminium Smelters.\r\n\r\n<b>Thickeners</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used to concentrate alumina Slurry (30-35% Solids) from refinery to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into circuit whereas the underflow is taken for evaporation circuit or to tailings as reject disposal.\r\n\r\n<b>Flotation </b>\r\n\r\nWe can offer the Beneficiation/Up gradation solution for the Bauxite ore through flotation as part of total solution for this plant which will include Crushing, Grinding, Flotation, thickening, dewatering     (Filtration), slurry pumping and system integration and plant design.', 'BAUXITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '623-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:24:25', '2015-02-02 00:24:25', '', 623, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/623-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(695, 2, '2015-02-02 00:35:43', '2015-02-02 00:35:43', 'MSEL caters to OEM supply, service and job-shop manufacturing needs of all the components of power sector e.g.\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\n	<li>Thermal (Coal Fired)</li>\n	<li>Thermal (Gas Fired)</li>\n	<li>Nuclear</li>\n	<li>Solar</li>\n	<li>Wind</li>\n</ul>\nIn thermal power stations we have three sections e.g.-\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\n	<li>Coal/Lignite Handling</li>\n</ul>\nFor MSEL footprints in this section we can refer to <a href="Coal &amp; Lignite.docx">Coal/Lignite</a> sectors of Industry.\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\n	<li>Ash Handling</li>\n</ul>\nMSEL can supply following equipment for this sector.\n<ol style="margin-left:25px;">\n	<li>Transporter Vessel</li>\n	<li>Rotary Drum Mixer</li>\n	<li>Paddle Mixer</li>\n	<li>Ash Intake Valve</li>\n	<li>Air Intake Valve</li>\n	<li>Cup Valve</li>\n	<li>Dual Disc Valve</li>\n	<li>Clinker Crusher</li>\n	<li>Bag Filter</li>\n	<li>Cyclone Separator</li>\n	<li>Centrifugal Ash Slurry Pumps</li>\n	<li>Sump Pumps</li>\n	<li>Drag Chain Conveyors</li>\n</ol>\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\n	<li>Balance of Power\n<ol style="margin-left:25px;">\n	<li>Water Pumps</li>\n	<li>Job Shop Manufactured Items</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ul>\nIn Gas Fired, Nuclear, Solar and Wind Power Sector MSEL is in position to undertake Job-Shop Manufacture of items, equipment and components of equipment as per customer’s drawings and specs.', 'POWER', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '629-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:35:43', '2015-02-02 00:35:43', '', 629, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/629-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(697, 2, '2015-02-02 00:34:11', '2015-02-02 00:34:11', 'MSEL caters to OEM supply, service and job-shop manufacturing needs of all the components of power sector e.g.\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Thermal (Coal Fired)</li>\r\n	<li>Thermal (Gas Fired)</li>\r\n	<li>Nuclear</li>\r\n	<li>Solar</li>\r\n	<li>Wind</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn thermal power stations we have three sections e.g.-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Coal/Lignite Handling</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor MSEL footprints in this section we can refer to <a href="Coal &amp; Lignite.docx">Coal/Lignite</a> sectors of Industry.\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Ash Handling</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMSEL can supply following equipment for this sector.\r\n<ol style="margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Transporter Vessel</li>\r\n	<li>Rotary Drum Mixer</li>\r\n	<li>Paddle Mixer</li>\r\n	<li>Ash Intake Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Air Intake Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Cup Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Dual Disc Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Clinker Crusher</li>\r\n	<li>Bag Filter</li>\r\n	<li>Cyclone Separator</li>\r\n	<li>Centrifugal Ash Slurry Pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Sump Pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Drag Chain Conveyors</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Balance of Power\r\n<ol style="margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Water Pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Job Shop Manufactured Items</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn Gas Fired, Nuclear, Solar and Wind Power Sector MSEL is in position to undertake Job-Shop Manufacture of items, equipment and components of equipment as per customer’s drawings and specs.', 'POWER', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '629-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:34:11', '2015-02-02 00:34:11', '', 629, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/629-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(698, 2, '2015-02-02 00:35:43', '2015-02-02 00:35:43', 'MSEL caters to OEM supply, service and job-shop manufacturing needs of all the components of power sector e.g.\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Thermal (Coal Fired)</li>\r\n	<li>Thermal (Gas Fired)</li>\r\n	<li>Nuclear</li>\r\n	<li>Solar</li>\r\n	<li>Wind</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn thermal power stations we have three sections e.g.-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Coal/Lignite Handling</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor MSEL footprints in this section we can refer to <a href="Coal &amp; Lignite.docx">Coal/Lignite</a> sectors of Industry.\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Ash Handling</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMSEL can supply following equipment for this sector.\r\n<ol style="margin-left:25px;">\r\n	<li>Transporter Vessel</li>\r\n	<li>Rotary Drum Mixer</li>\r\n	<li>Paddle Mixer</li>\r\n	<li>Ash Intake Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Air Intake Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Cup Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Dual Disc Valve</li>\r\n	<li>Clinker Crusher</li>\r\n	<li>Bag Filter</li>\r\n	<li>Cyclone Separator</li>\r\n	<li>Centrifugal Ash Slurry Pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Sump Pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Drag Chain Conveyors</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Balance of Power\r\n<ol style="margin-left:25px;">\r\n	<li>Water Pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Job Shop Manufactured Items</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn Gas Fired, Nuclear, Solar and Wind Power Sector MSEL is in position to undertake Job-Shop Manufacture of items, equipment and components of equipment as per customer’s drawings and specs.', 'POWER', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '629-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:35:43', '2015-02-02 00:35:43', '', 629, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/629-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(706, 2, '2015-02-02 00:43:52', '2015-02-02 00:43:52', 'With production units at Kumardhubi (I and II), Asansol, Baroda and Bangalore, MSEL is well equipped to undertake job shop manufacturing of items, equipment and or machine components, vessels, heavy structural etc. to customer’s drawings and specifications. Our facilities are approved by major third party inspection agencies like Lloyds, TPE, TUV etc. Some of major items manufactured by us for Steel Plants are listed below-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Primary Gas Cooler</li>\r\n	<li>Dewatering Drum</li>\r\n	<li>In Burden Probe, Distribution Rockers and Bleeder Valves</li>\r\n	<li>Strand Guide Roller Block, Run-out Roller Table, and Billet Lifting Device</li>\r\n	<li>Tail End Pinch Rolls, Cutting Approach Roller Table</li>\r\n	<li>Ladle Stand, Teeming Ladle and Ladle Transfer Car</li>\r\n	<li>Coke Oven &amp; By Product Equipment</li>\r\n	<li>Electrode Arms, Mast and lance for Lancing Furnace</li>\r\n	<li>Ducting and Gas Cooler Primary Scrubbers</li>\r\n	<li>Rail Mill Transfer Car, Billet and Bloom Caster</li>\r\n	<li>Slab Charging Buffer and Grate</li>\r\n	<li>Tube Heat Exchangers, Low Pressure and High Pressure Boilers</li>\r\n	<li>Sulphur Condensers and Process Gas Heater</li>\r\n	<li>Tundish, Scrap Bucket and Scrap Box Transfer Car</li>\r\n	<li>Machined and Tooth Cut Gears up to 8 M diameters</li>\r\n	<li>Reconditioning of HP/LP Feeder for Paper Industry.</li>\r\n	<li>Rotary Kiln components e.g. Shell, Slide Shoe, and Base Frame etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Components for Paddle Feeders, Bucket Wheel Stackers &amp; Reclaimers, Bucket Wheel Stacker Components.</li>\r\n	<li>Penstocks and Gates for Hydro-electric Plants.</li>\r\n	<li>Autogenous and Semi-autogenous grinding mills.</li>\r\n	<li>Butt Extractors for Anode Plants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPower Roller Conveyors and Gravity Roller Conveyors.', 'JOBBING', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '637-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 00:43:52', '2015-02-02 00:43:52', '', 637, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/637-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(707, 2, '2015-02-02 01:22:22', '2015-02-02 01:22:22', 'Aggregate Production is consisting of following activities-\r\n\r\n<b>Extraction</b>\r\n\r\nStripping\r\n\r\nDrilling &amp; Blasting\r\n\r\nShot Rock or Gravel Bank creation\r\n\r\n<b>Crushing</b>\r\n\r\nScalping\r\n\r\nPrimary Crushing\r\n\r\nSecondary &amp; tertiary crushing\r\n\r\nImpact Crushing\r\n\r\n<b>Screening</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Sand Production</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Segregation</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Stockpiling &amp; Handling</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Retrieval</b>\r\n\r\nFollowing MSEL equipment cater to above processes in Aggregate Production-\r\n\r\n<b>Apron Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size rocks from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at quarry end Stone Handling.\r\n\r\n<b>Jaw Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used as primary crushers in aggregate production. Either Single Toggles or Double Toggle Jaw Crushers are selected based on hardness and mineralogy of stones.\r\n\r\n<b>Roll Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nToothed Double Roll Crushers are used as secondary crushers in aggregate plants to crush (-) 25 mm size. Smooth DR Crushers can be used for crushing up to (-) 5mm for soft and medium soft rocks.\r\n\r\n<b>Cone Crushers</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell these equipment, which are required in tertiary crushing (-30/10 mm) of stones for subsequent reduction to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\n<b>Bucket Elevators</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used for vertical transport of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, sand, grits etc.\r\n\r\n<b>Conveyor Components</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<b>Reciprocating Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse Stones and normal versions for fine Stones.\r\n\r\n<b>Rotary Disc Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material e.g. river bed gravel, sand, alumina etc. from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment.\r\n\r\n<b>Grizzly Screens/ Feeders</b>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Quarry Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Crusher to separate undersized and oversized Stone. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim Stone from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<b>Circular Motion Screens</b>\r\n\r\nAlso known as CM Screens, these are used to segregate various size fractions in Stone streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers<b>. </b>These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<b>Linear Motion Screens</b>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>High Particle Acceleration Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for heavy and very heavy screening applications for fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul style="list-style:disc; margin-left:15px;">\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Banana Screens</b>\r\n\r\nThese are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<b>Mobile &amp; Semi-mobile Crushing &amp; Screening Plants</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL has a large range of skid mounted and wheel mounted Crushing &amp; Screening plants in various configurations to suit multiplicity of sized products in various capacities catering to production of coarse, medium and fine aggregates and road stratum material.\r\n\r\nFor Infrastructure sector MSEL offers following equipment\r\n\r\n<b>Dry Mortar Mixing Plants</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL-NFLG Dry Mortar Mixing Plants are environment friendly and characterised by High Efficiency, Low Energy Consumption. The range Tower, Ladder and Station configurations covering a production range of 5 t/h to 80 t/h.\r\n\r\n<b>Concrete Batching Plants</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL-NFLG Concrete Batching Plants are available in in Station and Tower configurations covering production capacity range of 50 t/h to 270 t/h.\r\n\r\n<b>Asphalt Mixing Plants</b>\r\n\r\nOur offerings in this sector cover mobile plants of 90 to 120 t/h and stationery plants of 80 to 400 t/h production capacities.\r\n\r\n<b>Mobile Concrete Mixing Plants</b>\r\n\r\nMSEL-NFLG mobile concrete mixing plants are available in 50, 75 and 100 m3/h capacities.\r\n\r\n<b>Sand Washing Plant:</b>\r\n\r\nWe can offer the sand washing plant with the water recovery equipment for the best quality of sand production with conservation of environment. We can offer the customised solution for any size/ capacity as most of the equipment used in this plant ie Thickener, Slurry pump and Filtration System are our regular product.\r\n\r\n<b>Stone Cutting and Polishing Plant</b>\r\n\r\nWe can give total solution for the slurry handling and ETP of the stone industry. We have the slurry pumps for the Grit recirculation, vertical slurry pumps for the water collection/ pumping, settlers, Flocculent dosing system and filter press under one roof.', 'AGGREGATE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '631-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-02 01:22:22', '2015-02-02 01:22:22', '', 631, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/631-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
