(869, 2, '2015-05-19 07:41:18', '2015-05-19 07:41:18', '<div class="con-block" style="text-align: justify;">\n\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-192" src="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/vadodara-unit-300x116.jpg" alt="vadodara-unit" width="300" height="116" />The <strong>Vadodara</strong> unit is located at Savli in GIDC complex and has a land area of 100,700 m² with 42,500 m² covered. The region falls on the Savli-Halol route of the Delhi Mumbai Investment Corridor (DMIC), NH 8. Savli has been recognised as a location for Export Promotion Industrial Park (EPIP) which is proposed to be elevated to the Special Economic Zone (SEZ). The nearest deep sea port is Dahej, 150 kms away and the nearest airport is Vadodara, 14 kms away.\n\nThis unit has four bays each 26 mtr wide and 150 m long with 13 m hook height and 100 tons crane handling facility.The flooring is of RCC tri-mix capable of handling large loads. The open yard is approximately 35000 sqmtrs. Apart from the manufacturing bays, the unit has a fully furnished Office Block of 1082 sqmtrs and a separate modern canteen block. Power connection is from 33 kV HT line through a 1000 kVA transformer.\n\nThe unit is ISO 9001 certified.\n\nThis unit has a dedicated Design team and is equipped with all kinds of manufacturing facilities for fabrication, machining, assembly, inspection and testing.\n\nThe Vadodara unit manufactures “SAYAJI” brand of jaw crushers, roll crushers, hammer mills, impactors, coke cutters, various types of screens and wheel mounted crushing and screening plant.It has alsostarted manufacturing of Concrete Batching Plant, Asphalt Batching Plant and Dry Mortar Mixing Plant of various capacities with the technology provided by Fujian South Highway Machinery Co. Ltd. (NFLG).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>', 'Vadodara', 'The Vadodara unit is located at Savli in GIDC complex and has a land area of 100,700 m² with 42,500 m² covered.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '70-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-05-19 07:41:18', '2015-05-19 07:41:18', '', 70, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/70-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(870, 2, '2015-05-19 07:17:24', '2015-05-19 07:17:24', '<div class="con-block" style="text-align: justify;">\n\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-197" src="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/KumardhubiUnit-I-300x143.jpg" alt="KumardhubiUnit-I" width="300" height="143" />MBECL, the parent company of MSEL, started its business from this place in 1961. Kumardhubi is situated in the heart of coal belt in the state of Jharkhand and the factory was strategically set up to cater full services to the nearby coal washeries and iron ore mines. NH 2 is just 2.5 km away from the factory.\n\nWith a covered area of 18,750 m² out of 51,000 m², the Kumardhubi unit has 70 MT overhead load handling capacity, plate rolling facility of up to 120 mm thick, Vertical Boring Machine of work dia up to 8 mtrs, Skoda CNC Boring Machine with 8 mtrs travel, Gear Hobbing Machine up to 8 mtrs work diameter, dual head CNC Profile Cutting Machine, several Lathes up to 5 mtrs bed length and several other special purpose equipment for manufacturing grinding mills up to 5 mtrs dia, crushers, feeders and screens.\n\nThe Kumardhubi unit is an integrated unit having Engineering and Design, Marketing and Product Support, Purchase, Manufacturing, Assembly and QA under one roof to provide customers a total solution from Design to Installation and Commissioning. The unit has ISO 9001 and 14001 certification with NABL accreditation for its mechanical testing laboratory.\n\nKumardhubi unit manufactures all types of crushers, screens, grinding mills, feeders and other equipment for bulk material handling, port handling and ash handling. It has a rich experience of manufacturing many stacker cum reclaimers, the largest goliath crane in the country, bucket wheel excavators and one of the longest apron feeders in the world.\n\n<img class="ngg_displayed_gallery mceItem" src="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/nextgen-attach_to_post/preview/id--1163" alt="" data-mce-placeholder="1" />\n\n</div>', 'Kumardhubi', 'MBECL, the parent company of MSEL, started its business from this place in 1961.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '69-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-05-19 07:17:24', '2015-05-19 07:17:24', '', 69, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/69-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
